$AMD (April 30, 2026-monthly chart)

Over the past few days, as $AMD pulled back from its all-time high, several friends and influencers have trimmed their positions. It served as a timely reminder that many are still trading in and out — a mindset that often causes them to miss the much larger long-term rally.

No doubt, locking in profits totally makes sense, but true long-term wealth is NEVER built through constant short-term trading.

Zooming out on the monthly chart (panel 2), the green light recently flipped to red on the latest bar. Historically, this signal has often preceded multi-month uptrends. 

With this powerful GOD candle now in place, I expect (1) many traders will take profits while (2) retail investors who missed the move will not chase, fearing they’re buying the top.

Thankfully, our community was well-positioned for this. I first highlighted buys at $110 and continued adding non-stop all the way to $200. 

Unfortunately, I didn’t manage to perfectly time the absolute bottom at $76. Fortunately, holding a strong position of 24,888 shares is more than enough to ride the whale momentum going forward.

Position sizing matters far more than timing the perfect bottom. Timing the perfect bottom is nice, but it’s meaningless without sufficient size. A well-sized position in a strong trend will almost always outperform perfect timing with a tiny allocation.

The whales gave us nearly a full year to accumulate. At the end of the day, long-term investing demands discipline, strong holding power in the right names, and the buying power to keep adding during dips. That combination is what drives true compound gains. 

